status: Thembisile Dlamini RHM said the borehole was drilled 2015 and constructed 2016. She also stated that 30 households benefit from the borehole although the water is salty.
Borehole was constructed 2014 by DWA and covers 75 household. The water quality is good and the borehole was rehabilitated once since construction.
Borehole was constructed in 2000 and has not developed mechanical problems. It serves a total of 37 households.
Borehole was constructed by RSSC and DWA 2016 and the community was told that the borehole has more water Hence it will be pump tested. The water quality is good.

Borehole was constructed in 2017 by DWA and 45 homesteads benefit from the borehole. Borehole has not been rehabilitated since its construction. Pump testing was not done hence the community is not aware of the borehole yield.

Borehole was constructed in 2015 by DWA and Thirst and the beneficiaries are 80 household. Borehole was pump tested and found to have a lot of water hence it’s amongst the boreholes to be pump tested for the LSRWSS Project.

Majahonkhe Dlamini, water committee Chairperson said the borehole covers 55 homesteads and was constructed in 2016. The water from the borehole has a red colour which makes it hard for the community to use it for drinking.
subjective_quality: Not Portable (The water from the borehole has a red colour which makes it hard for the community to use for drinking.)

status: Borehole was constructed in 2002 through a donation by Wold Vision. It was rehabilitated once and it covers 70 households narrated Sibongile Ndzimandze.
